<div class="head_titles">
<h1 class="entry-title" title="Autographer uses five in-built sensors and OMG stop-motion tech to take photos without the intervention of button-mashing users">
New wearable camera automatically snaps its own pictures
<a href="#" class="addtowatchlist add awl-article" title="Add to ..." rel="" id="atwlArticleTitle">Add to ...</a>
</h1>
<div class="entry-meta">
<p class="creditline source-org vcard">Reuters</p>
<div class="dateline">
<p>Published <time datetime="2012-22-24T15:09:02Z" pubdate>Monday, Sep. 24 2012, 11:22 AM EDT</time></p>
<p>Last updated <time class="updated" datetime="2012-24-24T15:09:25Z" pubdate>Monday, Sep. 24 2012, 11:24 AM EDT</time></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</header>
<div class="entry-content fontsmall simplesans">
<div class="story_tools clearfix">
<div class="cmt">
<a title="Go to the comments page" href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/technology/gadgets-and-gear/gadgets/new-wearable-camera-automatically-snaps-its-own-pictures/article4563291/comments/">56 comments</a>
<span></span>
</div>
<ul class="share_tools">
<li>
<div id="tgamShareBar"></div>
</li>
<li class="article_print_tool">
<a href="http://www.theglobeandmail.com/technology/gadgets-and-gear/gadgets/new-wearable-camera-automatically-snaps-its-own-pictures/article4563291/?service=print" rel="nofollow" title="Print this page"><span
class="icon_article icon_article_print icon_article_print_gigya"
