</li>
<li id="article_text_tool">
<a href="#" class="typetrigger btn btn_light"><span>A</span>A</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
<div class="x140x460 clearfix">
<div class="column-1 gridcol">
<div class="widget_ad tile" id="tile1">
<script>
aPs="t1";
var t1AC=fnTkt('a'+'ai',120,240,ai,'j',nc);
document.write(t1AC);
</script>
</div>
</div>
<div class="column-2 gridcol">
<p>A groundbreaking camera that decides itself when to take a shot will go on sale in Britain in November, in the first consumer application of technology developed by the British maker OMG Plc.</p><p>The device, called the Autographer, uses five in-built sensors and software developed by Microsoft Corp to chose the best moment to capture an image without any intervention from the user.</p>
<aside class="entry-related lt1484 ">
<h4>More Related to this Story</h4>
<ul>
